                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d121">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.34119/95: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Chargé in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="77" xml:id="d121fn77">The same, <hi rend="italic">mutatis
                            mutandis</hi>, August 12, 5 p.m., to the Minister in Bolivia, as
                        telegram No. 24.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-08-12T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 12, 1935—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>15. Reference Gibson’s 168, August 11, 9 p.m. to the Department. Please express
                    orally to the Foreign Minister the hope of this Government that the Paraguayan
                    Government will see its way to accept without change the agreement on prisoners
                    of war, which seems eminently fair to both sides.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
